text.tspan: Hardworking lead patient coordinator bringing proven direct support experience developed during
healthcare career. Knowledgeable about paperwork procedures, mobility assistance and documentation
requirements. Team-oriented and adaptable to changing needs.
Assist in locating funding for particular procedures or other patient needs.
Collect patient data and documented records of health conditions, hospitalizations and lifestyle
Coordinate care for 10+ patients, oversee admission processes and manage patient flows each day.
Educated 20+ patients and caregivers on discharge instructions to sustain patient health and drive
Collaborated with interdisciplinary healthcare professionals to develop and modify individualized care
plans for patients in multiple units.
Discussed cost of service, insurance coverage and payment options with the patient.
Transcribed medical, legal, government, business and academic dictation with absolute accuracy.
Approached over 100 current and future patient inquiries through phone, providing support in
Addressed patient, partner and insurance company inquiries through email, helping to troubleshoot
scheduling, payment, insurance and record release issues.
Certified Medical Administrative Assistant (CMAA), National Healthcareer Association - 2020
